data.metadata: {"description":"I‚Äôve known Pavil through the Pudgy/Abstract community since early 2024. What sets him apart is not only his style but his process. He starts with a short brief, quickly sends pencil sketches, agrees on a color palette, and then executes cleanly either on stream or offline.\nI first noticed him during live graffiti sessions on the Abstract portal: he turned multiple PFPs into cohesive, wall-ready compositions instead of just copying avatars. Later, at a local Pudgy meetup, he handled a live painting segment with clear preparation, no delays, and strong composition, and attendees ended up using the artwork as social headers.\nHis contribution to the community is real: he regularly supports Pudgy Russia, helps creators with custom pieces, and communicates professionally (fast replies, realistic timelines, no drama). If you need someone who delivers striking graffiti and represents the culture responsibly, Pavil is reliable and easy to recommend."}

translation.translatedDescription:
I‚Äôve known Pavil through the Pudgy/Abstract community since early 2024. What sets him apart is not only his style but his process. He starts with a short brief, quickly sends pencil sketches, agrees on a color palette, and then executes cleanly either on stream or offline.
I first noticed him during live graffiti sessions on the Abstract portal: he turned multiple PFPs into cohesive, wall-ready compositions instead of just copying avatars. Later, at a local Pudgy meetup, he handled a live painting segment with clear preparation, no delays, and strong composition, and attendees ended up using the artwork as social headers.
His contribution to the community is real: he regularly supports Pudgy Russia, helps creators with custom pieces, and communicates professionally (fast replies, realistic timelines, no drama). If you need someone who delivers striking graffiti and represents the culture responsibly, Pavil is reliable and easy to recommend.

translation.translatedDescription:
He's truly incredible, and I'm not just saying that to be nice. Pavil is a well-known figure within Abstract because he accomplished something unprecedented; no one has done anything like it before. He has a definite talent for street art. 

Indeed, Pavil has created several murals using his talent to illustrate the various projects on Abstract, on a wall in the middle of the street.

He did this live, during a stream on Abstract, followed by several hundred people. You really have to go see his performance; it's breathtaking.

He repeated this by creating other street artworks on the same theme (Abstract Ecosystem).

He's a gigachad within Abstract, and he has more than earned this title, given his commitment and talent.
